{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place flour, 1 tsp salt and ½ tsp pepper in a bag and shake well to combine. Add chicken thighs to bag and toss until well coated in seasoned flour.","Heat 3-4 Tbsp oil in a large oven-proof casserole dish then fry floured chicken until golden on all sides. Set aside.","Preheat oven to 180°C. Place onions, celery, carrots and 15 g oil in mixing bowl then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 4.5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add stock, thyme, ¼ tsp salt and ¼ tsp pepper then cook <b>8 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add potatoes to casserole dish, then cover with prepared vegetable broth. Bake for 50-60 minutes (180°C) until potatoes and chicken are cooked.","Remove casserole dish from oven and stir in peas. Replace lid and allow to rest for 5 minutes before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["50 g plain flour","1 ¼ tsp fine sea salt","¾ tsp ground black pepper","8 chicken thighs, with skin","15 g olive oil, plus 3-4 Tbsp for frying","200 g onions, quartered","160 g celery stalks, cut in pieces","320 g carrots, cut in pieces","800 g chicken stock","2 sprigs fresh thyme","650 - 800 g potatoes, peeled, cut in pieces (2 cm)","200 g frozen green peas"]}],"id":"r87541","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-UQUQ4LZf1vg\/XZQwHYnzF9I\/AAAAAAAAcjA\/Fu78Du7ts6U_HZjvtz8DqLvUM-xNu_czACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_TvgzX6sSBU4wuC55.png","title":"Spring Chicken Casserole","publishedAt":"2015-11-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"24.8 g","fat":"29.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"28 g","calories":"1984 kJ \/ 474 kcal"},"usefulItems":"medium food bag, casserole dish, hob, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Also works well served with steamed rice. Omit potatoes and place 300 g rice in internal steaming basket above 1000 g water. Steam <strong>22 min\/Varoma\/speed 3<\/strong>.","This easy recipe can be frozen for up to 6 months, just omit the peas. Cook then allow to cool before freezing. To re-heat, allow to defrost then reheat in oven, adding a little stock if needed, for 30-40 minutes until chicken is tender, adding frozen peas 5 minutes before serving."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 30m","8 portions"]}